The Template Method Pattern

DESCRIPTION

The View class defines a template to show contents. It defines the fixed steps 
to display the view and implement the invariant parts. HtmlView subclass provide 
a doDisplay() operation and let the parent call it. In this way, the subclass
provide a hook for the parent to invoke.

BUILD & RUN

    g++ Client.cpp View.cpp HtmlView.cpp
    ./a.out

PROBLEMS

The Template Method pattern is import in refactoring. 
